Document: RDPipelineColorBlendStateAttachment
Path: godot/classes/class_rdpipelinecolorblendstateattachment.rst
Summary: Configures color blending operations for rendering pipelines in Godot's RenderingDevice.

Inherits: Object

This class controls how blending between source and destination fragments is performed when using RenderingDevice.

GDScript:
    # Mix blend mode
    var attachment = RDPipelineColorBlendStateAttachment.new()
    attachment.enable_blend = true
    attachment.color_blend_op = RenderingDevice.BLEND_OP_ADD
    attachment.src_color_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_SRC_ALPHA
    attachment.dst_color_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA
    attachment.alpha_blend_op = RenderingDevice.BLEND_OP_ADD
    attachment.src_alpha_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ONE
    attachment.dst_alpha_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA

GDScript:
    # Add blend mode
    var attachment = RDPipelineColorBlendStateAttachment.new()
    attachment.enable_blend = true
    attachment.alpha_blend_op = RenderingDevice.BLEND_OP_ADD
    attachment.color_blend_op = RenderingDevice.BLEND_OP_ADD
    attachment.src_color_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_SRC_ALPHA
    attachment.dst_color_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ONE
    attachment.src_alpha_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_SRC_ALPHA
    attachment.dst_alpha_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ONE

GDScript:
    # Subtract blend mode
    var attachment = RDPipelineColorBlendStateAttachment.new()
    attachment.enable_blend = true
    attachment.alpha_blend_op = RenderingDevice.BLEND_OP_REVERSE_SUBTRACT
    attachment.color_blend_op = RenderingDevice.BLEND_OP_REVERSE_SUBTRACT
    attachment.src_color_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_SRC_ALPHA
    attachment.dst_color_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ONE
    attachment.src_alpha_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_SRC_ALPHA
    attachment.dst_alpha_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ONE

GDScript:
    # Multiply blend mode
    var attachment = RDPipelineColorBlendStateAttachment.new()
    attachment.enable_blend = true
    attachment.alpha_blend_op = RenderingDevice.BLEND_OP_ADD
    attachment.color_blend_op = RenderingDevice.BLEND_OP_ADD
    attachment.src_color_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_DST_COLOR
    attachment.dst_color_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ZERO
    attachment.src_alpha_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_DST_ALPHA
    attachment.dst_alpha_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ZERO

GDScript:
    # Pre-multiplied alpha blend mode
    var attachment = RDPipelineColorBlendStateAttachment.new()
    attachment.enable_blend = true
    attachment.alpha_blend_op = RenderingDevice.BLEND_OP_ADD
    attachment.color_blend_op = RenderingDevice.BLEND_OP_ADD
    attachment.src_color_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ONE
    attachment.dst_color_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA
    attachment.src_alpha_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ONE
    attachment.dst_alpha_blend_factor = RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA
---CHUNK---
Document: RDPipelineColorBlendStateAttachment
Path: godot/classes/class_rdpipelinecolorblendstateattachment.rst
Summary: Defines the properties for color blending in a rendering pipeline attachment.

Properties:
* alpha_blend_op (BlendOperation): The blend operation for the alpha channel. Default: 0.
* color_blend_op (BlendOperation): The blend operation for the color channels. Default: 0.
* dst_alpha_blend_factor (BlendFactor): The destination blend factor for the alpha channel. Default: 0.
* dst_color_blend_factor (BlendFactor): The destination blend factor for the color channels. Default: 0.
* enable_blend (bool): Enables or disables color blending. Default: false.
* src_alpha_blend_factor (BlendFactor): The source blend factor for the alpha channel. Default: 0.
* src_color_blend_factor (BlendFactor): The source blend factor for the color channels. Default: 0.
* write_a (bool): Enables or disables writing to the alpha channel. Default: true.
* write_b (bool): Enables or disables writing to the blue channel. Default: true.
* write_g (bool): Enables or disables writing to the green channel. Default: true.
* write_r (bool): Enables or disables writing to the red channel. Default: true.
---CHUNK---
