Document: RDPipelineColorBlendStateAttachment
Path: godot/classes/class_rdpipelinecolorblendstateattachment.rst
Summary: Defines the properties for color blending operations in a rendering pipeline attachment.

Property: alpha_blend_op
Type: BlendOperation
Description: The blend mode to use for the alpha channel.
Default: 0

Property: color_blend_op
Type: BlendOperation
Description: The blend mode to use for the red/green/blue color channels.
Default: 0

Property: dst_alpha_blend_factor
Type: BlendFactor
Description: Controls how the blend factor for the alpha channel is determined based on the destination's fragments.
Default: 0

Property: dst_color_blend_factor
Type: BlendFactor
Description: Controls how the blend factor for the color channels is determined based on the destination's fragments.
Default: 0

Property: enable_blend
Type: bool
Description: If true, performs blending between the source and destination according to the factors defined in src_color_blend_factor, dst_color_blend_factor, src_alpha_blend_factor and dst_alpha_blend_factor. The blend modes color_blend_op and alpha_blend_op are also taken into account, with write_r, write_g, write_b and write_a controlling the output.
Default: false

Property: src_alpha_blend_factor
Type: BlendFactor
Description: Controls how the blend factor for the alpha channel is determined based on the source's fragments.
Default: 0

Property: src_color_blend_factor
Type: BlendFactor
Description: Controls how the blend factor for the color channels is determined based on the source's fragments.
Default: 0

Property: write_a
Type: bool
Description: If true, writes the new alpha channel to the final result.
Default: true

Property: write_b
Type: bool
Description: If true, writes the new blue color channel to the final result.
Default: true

Property: write_g
Type: bool
Description: If true, writes the new green color channel to the final result.
Default: true

Property: write_r
Type: bool
Description: If true, writes the new red color channel to the final result.
Default: true
---CHUNK---
Document: RDPipelineColorBlendStateAttachment
Path: godot/classes/class_rdpipelinecolorblendstateattachment.rst
Summary: Configures a single color blend state attachment for a render pipeline.

Method: set_as_mix() → void
Convenience method to perform standard mix blending with straight (non-premultiplied) alpha. This sets enable_blend to true, src_color_blend_factor to RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_SRC_ALPHA, dst_color_blend_factor to RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA, src_alpha_blend_factor to RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_SRC_ALPHA and dst_alpha_blend_factor to RenderingDevice.BLEND_FACTOR_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA.